<img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1803/432776-625x325.png?2" alt="Applications open for Top Tech Tools for Women in Business" width="625" height="325" align="left">The programme aims to see female entrepreneurs empowered by offering them strategic support in an environment where they can receive guidance on how to effectively deploy the tech tools that are most appropriate for their businesses.<img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1610/364508-120x120.jpg?2" alt="Thomson Reuters innovation lab opens in Cape Town" width="120" height="120">Thomson Reuters innovation lab opens in Cape TownMass media and information firm Thomson Reuters has announced the launch of Thomson Reuters Labs at Bandwidth Barn in Woodstock...17 Oct 2016Who should apply?According to the programme organisers, apply for this course if: you are the CEO or founder of your own businessyour business has been running for at least a yearyou use tech in your business (e.g. Twitter, Trello) and want to learn to use it more effectivelyyou have a desire to implement a tech strategy in your businessyou have at least one staff member (permanent or part-time)you are based in the Western Capeyou are a woman who wants to use education to "kick her business up a notch".For more, go to www.citi-womeninbusiness.co.za.